    <div class="blog-container">
        <div class="upper-part">
            <h1 class="blog-title ng-binding">Saudi Arabia (KSA) Calorie Labels on Menus</h1>
            <div class="blog-header">
                <div class="nutrical-image">
                    <img src="images/Nutrical-logo-round-container.png">
                    <span class="blog-publisher">Nutrical Team</span>
                </div>
                <span class="blog-date ng-binding">Posted On Fri Apr 17 2020</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="results" ng-bind-html="content" class="ng-binding"><p><span style="font-weight: 400;"><img src="https://s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/ff-dubai/entity_images/images/000/000/497/big/image1.png?1587115268" alt="" width="800" height="530"></span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In Saudi Arabia, it is mandatory for restaurants and cafes to display calories for the food they serve.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">This initiative was launched by the Saudi Food &amp; Drug Authority in 2019 with the purpose of tackling rising obesity levels in the country.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The law applies to-</span></p>
<ol>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Restaurants and cafes</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Ice cream parlours</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Juice and fresh fruit vendors</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bakeries</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sweets shops</span></li>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cafeterias</span></li>
</ol>
<p>Where should information be displayed?</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Cash counters and desks, physical menus and menu boards, drive-thrus, phone and web applications.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">With NutriCal Health &amp; Nutrition Software, you can easily calculate calories, macronutrients and other nutrients of your food recipes based on the ingredients and serving sizes used. </span><a href="https://www.nutrical.co/how-it-works.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">(How?)</span></a></p>
<p><a href="https://www.nutrical.co/contact-us.html"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sign up for a 5 day free trial today and use the easy calorie calculator to see to generate nutritional information for your recipes!</span></a></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Email us on </span><a href="mailto:info@nutrical.co"><span style="font-weight: 400;">info@nutrical.co</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> or call / whatsapp us on + 971 52 994 1190 for more information.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">Source- The National Article, January 2019</span></p></div>
    </div>
